The paper deals with optimization problems involving set functions, which are commonly studied in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The use of the secretary problem as a framework for these problems also suggests a connection to decision theory and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are a common topic in machine learning and theoretical computer science (cs.LG). Finally, the paper introduces a new parameter, the supermodular degree, which is defined in terms of information theory and has been previously studied in the context of approximation algorithms (cs.IT).
